    "body": "I have this in my packages.yaml\r\n\r\n```yaml\r\n  python:\r\n    version: [2.7.13]\r\n```\r\n\r\nand also explicitly install python@3.6.0 to provide a particular version for version 3.\r\n\r\nSnakemake depends on `python@3.3:`, so it just pulled in `python@3.6.1`\r\n\r\nIs there anyway to also pin a version for Python 3?  \r\n\r\nMy best idea to avoid ending up with two copies of Python 3 is to find the things that I'm installing that depend on it and wire them up individually.  There aren't that many so it's not the end of the world, but I'm just checking to see if there's something more elegant I can do.",
